tter 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> buy a 2hb....you will want to keep all those skills up....it's a pain to bring em up if you are going to go from 60ish to 200+ when you hit 60 or so.<br><br>don't need anything fancy....just something to train with....<br><br> <p><center><b>yakov</b></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>          <font size="-5">[Grandmaster]</font></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font size="1"><br>          <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15746" target="new">profile</a></font></font>         </p>         </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucelestreya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestreya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 7:20:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should i buy better 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> Your 1HB weapons are fine, I used the GSC / CoT combo until at least level 45 and didn't have any problems. If you want to train up your 2HB (which is a good idea) get a Bamboo Bo Stick for 50-100pp and use that to train with.<br><br>1HB will prolly serve you better until you reach 50+, as that is when the higher damage bonus on 2HBs really starts to take off and help you do a lot more damage, and avoid ripostes among other things. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264371">Celestreya Eridani</a> -- 49th Monk of the Ashen Order, Quellious Server</center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswysh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swysh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 7:29:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should i buy better 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> 2HB is the bomb imo.<br><br>Also, one of the best weapons to have in your bag of tricks is the IFS and it's relatively cheap when you compare it to one handers that have the same staying power as you level. Get a fast 2hb is train up with then start trying to get a nice one post 50ish. Need to get leveled to see how nice the 2hbs are too. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40638>Swysh's Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uscaliagluon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scalia Gluon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 7:38:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should i buy better 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> After looking at your Magelo profile, I don't think that at this point you are likely to be able to afford a 2HB weapon that would be in the same league as your 1HB weapons, especially that GSC. I'd stick with 1HB and upgrade the armor as follows:<br><br>1. Face: Go kill an Iksar Pariah in WW or LoIO and loot his NO DROP AC 5 mask. Don't forget to take it off before you sell to vendors (CHA -25).<br><br>2. Put something in the Neck and Feet slots. An Ulthork Collar is AC 7 and HP 30 and you should be able to find it for 50pp or so. Wu's or Spore Covered for the Feet slot.<br><br>3. Wrists: Get rid of the AC 1 Serpentine Bracers (they are SO 1999! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and get Wu's or better if you can afford it.<br><br>4. Get two Gem Encrusted Steins (CHA 25, about 20pp per) if you don't have them already and put them in the bank.<br><br>5. Now go to Crystal Caverns and fight Orcs close to the Dwarf town. Solo or grouped, it doesn't matter. There is a guide on the Guide board here if you haven't been to CC before. You can do Miners and Watchmen no problem, Oracles may be a little problematic given your equipment. Loot Watchmen's weapons and sell with Sneak (3-6pp for Velium weapons, 19-27pp for Frozen ones). Loot all gems and sell them as well. Do not sell the small/regular/large pieces/bricks of Velium to the vendors. Either wait for higher level characters to auction for Velium or go the Bazaar and sell it yourself. Depending on your server's economy, Velium may bring you between 10pp for stackable pieces and 100pp for Large unstackable ones.<br><br>Rinse and repeat. By the time you are 40, Orcs will be easy and you will have some nice AC/HP gear. A few Orcs are still light blue at 45, as I recall, and extremely easy, so you can farm them for a long time if you are so inclined. Otherwise start grouping Spiders (sils sell well) and soloing/grouping stalag terrors in the Broken Bridge Room, then move onto the Geonids, who drop gems worth up to 190pp. You'll be one rich Monk by the time you are done with CC <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71792 target=_blank>Scalia</a> /  <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71783 target =_blank>Gluon</a> on E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 12:03:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should i buy better 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Do not sell the small/regular/large pieces/bricks of Velium to the vendors. Either wait for higher level characters to auction for Velium or go the Bazaar and sell it yourself. Depending on your server's economy, Velium may bring you between 10pp for stackable pieces and 100pp for Large unstackable ones.<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>I just set ALL forms of velium to 35pp in bazaar (Yes even pieces .. ESPECIALLY pieces!), shout Korph's Velium shop is OPEN! and afk.  Maybe shout again if I'm not sold out within half an hour.  Also, I look to see if anyone's selling velium cheaper, buy out their stocks and then sell at my price.  This is a great way to make platinum while killing orcs, and an excellent alternative to farming geonids if they're camped.<br><br>I think your top priority for equipment should be a haste item.  Anything 20+% will do.  After that, replace your bracers with something like Acrylia.  While in Crystal Caverns try to snag a Chipped Velium Amulet, (4AC 4str 30hp .1wt) which drops off stalag terrors deeper in (It's lore and often rots).<br><br>Edit spelling/grammar <p>-Korph<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308735"><img src="http://gjband.com/Sig.jpg"><br>Level 51 Disciple</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A> at: 9/23/02 12:04:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uboysenberrypineapplehead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boysenberry Pineapplehead</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 5:17:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should i buy better 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> Reguardless of gear or level, i say train your 2hb at all times.  If possible, get a Bamboo Bo Stick (8/20 2hb) and use that to get the skill ups.  The best time, is if u are on a large scale raid and u are not the puller.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>One day, u will get a NICE 2hb, and it SUKES if your skills is low.<br><br>On a side note, I was a &quot;well, im never gunna get a 2hb&quot; monk.  Then one day, i got a good deal on Tstaff.  I was SO happy.  Then i checked my 2hb skill.  It was an 8...  I was SO sad.  So, i started to fight mobs going from 8-250.  It was not fun.<br><br>I eventually got fed up, and went to the guild trainer.  I trained my 2hb skill from 50-250, lol.  It cost me 3 or 4k to get that skill!!!  WHO PAYS 4k for skill!!! <br><br>Moral of the story:  Don't be like Boysen.   <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=123128>Boysen's Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/23/02 8:29:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2rnxn/images/yorienko_avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should i buy better 1hb or begin to train 2hb?</span><hr size=1> I sworn to myself that I won't use 2HB until verant fix the 2HB animation :-)<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=11547.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=11547.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11547.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.emailToFriend?topicID=11547.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.threadControl?topicID=11547.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11547.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11547.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop recei